## Decision Guide: When to Use What

### Use Pydantic Schema When:

✅ Defining API contract (request/response structure)
✅ Type safety is important
✅ OpenAPI documentation needs clear schemas
✅ Request body validation (before DRF)
✅ Response serialization (after DRF)
✅ Query parameter validation

### Use DRF Serializer When:

✅ Creating/updating database models
✅ Complex nested object handling
✅ Business rule validation
✅ Database field mapping
✅ Computed/read-only fields
✅ Related object serialization

### Use Both When:

✅ You need type safety AND database operations
✅ You want clear API contracts AND complex validation
✅ You need OpenAPI docs AND business logic

